---
title: Miso-Honey Glazed Salmon with Spicy Roasted Veggie Jumble & Sesame Seeds
description: Sweet honey and salty-savory miso make a delicious glaze for juicy chicken cutlets! So delicious, in fact, that there’s plenty left over to drizzle over the accompanying jumble of roasted Brussels sprouts, carrots, and onion sprinkled with nutty sesame seeds and a pinch of spicy Korean chili flakes. #glazefordays
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6627ce682fa454163f2118f2-d51eb3ad.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/662940fc8637342901e44310-en-US.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/miso-honey-glazed-salmon-662940fc8637342901e44310
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: East Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 670 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 34 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 360 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim
and quarter @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise (halve any smaller sprouts).
Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1}(halved and cut into ½-inch-thick wedges).

Toss carrots, Brussels sprouts, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large
drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} and @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon}
to taste; season with @salt{}.

Roast on top rack until carrots are tender and Brussels sprouts are lightly
charred, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced, whites separated from greens).
Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced).

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add salmon;
cook (skin sides down) until skin is crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}. Flip and cook
until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Transfer to a #plate{}.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Heat @butter{2%tablespoon} in pan used for salmon over medium heat. Add
scallion whites and garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @honey{2%teaspoon}, @miso sauce concentrate{1}, and ¼ cup water.
Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until glaze has thickened
slightly, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

> TIP: If glaze does not come together, stir in a splash of water.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Once veggies are done roasting, sprinkle with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon};
toss to coat.

Thinly slice salmon crosswise.

Divide salmon and veggies between #plates{}. Drizzle salmon with glaze and
sprinkle everything with scallion greens. Serve.